---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Greg Kemp | Senior Full-Stack Engineer"
  description="Greg Kemp is a senior full-stack engineer who builds complete products end-to-end. 10+ years shipping production software for global brands."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero d-flex align-items-center">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 data-aos="fade-up">
        I build products,<br />
        <span class="accent-text">end to end.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lead mt-3" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
        Senior full-stack engineer with 10+ years shipping production software.
        From database schema to production UI, for brands like Primark and
        SuperDry. Originally a mechanical engineer and fusion energy researcher.
      </p>
      <a
        href="#experience"
        class="btn btn-hero mt-4"
        data-aos="fade-up"
        data-aos-delay="200">See my work</a
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About -->
  <section id="about" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row align-items-center">
        <div class="col-md-3 text-center mb-4 mb-md-0">
          <img
            src="/assets/img/profile.jpg"
            alt="Me rescuing a tortoise from a road in Croatia"
            style="width: 160px; height: 160px; object-fit: cover"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-9">
          <h2 class="section-heading">About me</h2>
          <p>
            I studied mechanical engineering at Cardiff, then did a master's in
            fusion energy at York. Somewhere along the way I taught myself to
            code, discovered I was good at it, and never looked back.
          </p>
          <p>
            I've spent the last 11 years at one company, but that single tenure
            hides a lot of range: 6+ greenfield products built from scratch, a
            company rebrand and pivot, and clients ranging from Primark to
            Triumph Motorcycles. I've gone from junior developer to senior
            architect, and I now own technical direction for major systems in a
            small, fast-moving team.
          </p>
          <p>
            Based in Budapest. When I'm not coding I'm usually climbing, caving,
            or playing guitar.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Experience -->
  <section
    id="experience"
    class="alt-bg"
    style="background-color: var(--bg-light)"
    data-aos="fade-up"
  >
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-heading text-center">Experience</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading text-center">
        CORE (UK) Ltd &rarr; TariffTel &middot; Trade compliance software for
        global brands
      </p>

      <!-- Senior -->
      <div class="timeline-phase">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-date">2022 &ndash; Present</div>
        <div class="timeline-title">Senior Developer / Architect</div>
        <div class="row g-3">
          <div class="col-12">
            <div class="project-card">
              <h5>TariffTel 2.0</h5>
              <div class="project-meta">
                .NET 8/10 &middot; Angular 19 &middot; Clean Architecture &middot;
                CQRS &middot; SignalR &middot; Azure
              </div>
              <p>
                Ground-up rewrite of a 10+ year legacy platform. The old system
                was a mix of ASP.NET WebForms, WinForms, and millions of lines of
                business logic buried in SQL stored procedures across 10 separate
                database repositories. Designed the new architecture from scratch
                and built the full system in under a year with a small team.
                Real-time messaging via SignalR, enterprise SSO through Microsoft
                Entra ID, and shared NPM libraries enabling consistent logic
                across multiple frontends.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12">
            <div class="project-card">
              <h5>Master Data Management System</h5>
              <div class="project-meta">
                .NET 10 &middot; Angular 19 &middot; Tailwind &middot; Dapper
              </div>
              <p>
                New system built on .NET 10 with a custom CQRS dispatcher
                (replacing MediatR), Dapper for performance-critical queries, and
                a Tailwind-based Angular UI.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mid -->
      <div class="timeline-phase">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-date">2017 &ndash; 2022</div>
        <div class="timeline-title">Developer</div>
        <div class="row g-3">
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="project-card">
              <h5>Customs Connect</h5>
              <div class="project-meta">
                Azure Functions &middot; .NET &middot; Serverless
              </div>
              <p>
                Customs declaration software built for Primark. Rebuilt v2 as a
                fully serverless Azure Functions application, integrating with
                classification and supply chain systems to automate the
                declaration process.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="project-card">
              <h5>LEAF</h5>
              <div class="project-meta">
                MVC &middot; Azure Functions &middot; Sustainability
              </div>
              <p>
                Sustainability reporting platform tracking fibre origins for the
                SCAP scheme. Built from scratch with a small team. Adopted by
                Primark and being evaluated by SuperDry before their restructure.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12">
            <div class="project-card">
              <h5>TariffTel Essentials &amp; Premium</h5>
              <div class="project-meta">
                Angular &middot; .NET &middot; B2C / B2B
              </div>
              <p>
                Built TariffTel Essentials, a B2C customs classification web app.
                Later built TariffTel Premium (the B2B version) single-handedly,
                which laid the architectural groundwork for the eventual TariffTel
                2.0 rewrite.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Junior -->
      <div class="timeline-phase">
        <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
        <div class="timeline-date">2014 &ndash; 2017</div>
        <div class="timeline-title">Junior Developer</div>
        <div class="row g-3">
          <div class="col-12">
            <div class="project-card">
              <h5>Supply Chain &amp; Classification Software</h5>
              <div class="project-meta">
                Primark &middot; SuperDry &middot; Triumph Motorcycles
              </div>
              <p>
                Production supply chain and classification systems serving major
                UK and international brands. First greenfield project:
                sustainability reporting for Primark's SCAP fibre-origin
                programme.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tech Stack -->
  <section id="techstack" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-heading text-center">Tech</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading text-center">
        What I reach for most. I pick up new tools fast.
      </p>
      <div class="row justify-content-center g-4">
        {
          [
            ["dotnetcore/dotnetcore-original", ".NET"],
            ["csharp/csharp-original", "C#"],
            ["typescript/typescript-original", "TypeScript"],
            ["angularjs/angularjs-original", "Angular"],
            ["react/react-original", "React"],
            ["python/python-original", "Python"],
            ["nodejs/nodejs-original", "Node.js"],
            ["azure/azure-original", "Azure"],
            ["docker/docker-original", "Docker"],
            ["postgresql/postgresql-original", "PostgreSQL"],
            ["microsoftsqlserver/microsoftsqlserver-plain", "SQL Server"],
          ].map(([icon, label]) => (
            <div class="col-4 col-sm-3 col-md-2 text-center">
              <img
                src={`https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/devicons/devicon/icons/${icon}.svg`}
                alt={label}
                class="tech-icon"
              />
              <div class="tech-label-text">{label}</div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Side Projects -->
  <section
    id="projects"
    class="alt-bg"
    style="background-color: var(--bg-light)"
    data-aos="fade-up"
  >
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-heading text-center">Side Projects</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading text-center">
        Things I build outside of work to explore new stacks and ideas.
      </p>
      <div class="row g-4 justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="side-project-card">
            <h5>DevSync</h5>
            <div class="tech-label">
              Next.js 16 &middot; PostgreSQL &middot; Prisma &middot; NextAuth
            </div>
            <p>
              Multi-tenant snippet manager with team collaboration, RBAC,
              full-text search, GitHub OAuth, email invitations, and subscription
              tiers. Dockerized and production-ready.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="side-project-card">
            <h5>CodeMop</h5>
            <div class="tech-label">Python &middot; FastAPI &middot; PostgreSQL</div>
            <p>
              AI code review tool. Hooks into GitHub PRs via webhooks and suggests
              improvements automatically.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="side-project-card">
            <h5>EV Route Optimizer</h5>
            <div class="tech-label">Node.js &middot; React 19 &middot; Leaflet</div>
            <p>
              Full-stack EV journey planner. Express backend with GraphHopper and
              OpenChargeMap; React frontend with interactive maps.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-3">
          <div class="side-project-card">
            <h5>EV Fleet Platform</h5>
            <div class="tech-label">
              .NET 8 &middot; Python &middot; Google OR-Tools
            </div>
            <p>
              Polyglot microservices. .NET fleet management API paired with a
              Python/Flask optimization engine for vehicle routing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Bring -->
  <section id="approach" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-8">
          <h2 class="section-heading text-center">What I Bring</h2>
          <p class="section-subheading text-center">
            How colleagues and clients describe working with me.
          </p>
          <div class="bring-item">
            <div class="bring-icon"><i class="bi bi-box-seam"></i></div>
            <div>
              <h5>Ship complete products</h5>
              <p>
                Database to UI, auth to deployment, working solo or in a team. I
                own the full stack and deliver working software.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bring-item">
            <div class="bring-icon"><i class="bi bi-building"></i></div>
            <div>
              <h5>Design systems that last</h5>
              <p>
                Clean Architecture, CQRS, modular boundaries, tested and
                documented. I think about what happens in two years, not just two
                sprints.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bring-item">
            <div class="bring-icon"><i class="bi bi-wrench-adjustable"></i></div>
            <div>
              <h5>Pick up anything</h5>
              <p>
                C#, TypeScript, Python, React, Node. I'm not attached to a stack.
                Whatever the problem needs, I'll learn it and ship it.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="bring-item">
            <div class="bring-icon"><i class="bi bi-lightning"></i></div>
            <div>
              <h5>Move fast, don't cut corners</h5>
              <p>
                Docker, CI/CD, automated tests, and structured logging from day
                one. Speed and quality aren't a trade-off.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <section id="contact" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-heading text-center">Get in touch</h2>
      <p class="section-subheading text-center">
        Have a project or question? I'd like to hear from you.
      </p>
      <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <div class="col-lg-6">
          <div class="card p-4">
            <form
              action="https://formspree.io/f/xldlbqyj"
              method="POST"
              class="contact-form"
            >
              <div class="row g-3">
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <label for="name" class="form-label">Name</label>
                  <input
                    type="text"
                    class="form-control"
                    id="name"
                    name="name"
                    placeholder="Your name"
                    required
                    autocomplete="name"
                  />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6">
                  <label for="email" class="form-label">Email</label>
                  <input
                    type="email"
                    class="form-control"
                    id="email"
                    name="email"
                    placeholder="you@email.com"
                    required
                    autocomplete="email"
                  />
                </div>
                <div class="col-12">
                  <label for="message" class="form-label">Message</label>
                  <textarea
                    class="form-control"
                    id="message"
                    name="message"
                    rows="5"
                    placeholder="Type your message here..."
                    required></textarea>
                </div>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-submit w-100 mt-4">
                Send Message
              </button>
            </form>
            <div id="thankYouCard" style="display: none">
              <div class="card border-0 p-4 mt-3">
                <div class="card-body text-center">
                  <i
                    class="bi bi-check-circle-fill display-4 mb-3"
                    style="color: var(--deep-teal)"></i>
                  <h5 class="mb-2">Thank you for your message!</h5>
                  <p class="mb-0" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7)">
                    I'll get back to you as soon as possible.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="text-center mt-4">
              <p class="mb-0" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 0.95rem">
                Or email me directly:
                <a href="mailto:greg@kempgt.com" class="accent-link">greg@kempgt.com</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
